98Status%20of%20Tigers%3A%20Co-Predators%20and%20Prey%20in%20India%2C%202022%E2%80%99.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Findias-tiger-population-rises-to-3167-reveals-latest-census-data%5C%22%3Esummary%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20released%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20April%2C%20had%20estimated%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20tiger%20population%20stood%20at%203%2C167%20%E2%80%93%20an%20increase%20of%206.7%25%20from%20the%20previous%20census%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20full%20report%20was%20released%20recently%2C%20which%C2%A0estimates%20that%20the%20population%20density%20of%20tigers%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20Sundarban%20forests%20has%20reached%204.27%20per%20100%20square%20kilometres.%20That%20number%20is%20close%20to%20the%20mangrove%20forests%E2%80%99%20estimated%20carrying%20capacity%20of%204.68%20tigers%20per%20100%20square%20kilometres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20Sundarbans%20are%20bound%20by%20human%20habitation%20to%20their%20north%20and%20west%2C%20the%20report%20notes%2C%20an%20expanding%20tiger%20population%20can%20only%20move%20further%20east%20into%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20the%20forests%20(the%20Sundarbans%20border%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%20in%20the%20south).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20forests%20are%20situated%20along%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20delta%2C%20formed%20by%20the%20rivers%20Ganga%2C%20Brahmaputra%20and%20Meghna%2C%20and%20are%20divided%20among%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%2C%20with%20the%20latter%20accounting%20for%2058%25%20of%20their%20total%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20tigers%20are%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20only%20ones%20known%20to%20live%20in%20a%20mangrove%20habitat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPhotos%20from%20camera%20traps%20across%20the%20forests%20revealed%20the%20presence%20of%20100%20individual%20tigers%20as%20of%202022%20%E2%80%93%2081%20from%20the%20Sundarban%20Tiger%20Reserve%20and%2020%20from%20the%20adjoining%20South%2024%20Parganas%20district%20of%20West%20Bengal%20state%20(one%20tiger%20was%20common%20to%20both%20areas).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20says%20that%20while%20tigers%20may%20move%20into%20Bangladesh%20through%20select%20areas%20within%20the%20forest%2C%20the%20two%20neighbouring%20countries%20protect%20the%20animals%20using%20different%20parameters.%20Major%20parts%20of%20the%20Indian%20Sundarbans%20are%20under%20the%20highest%20protection%20and%20management%20regime%20associated%20with%20a%20tiger%20reserve%2C%20with%20some%20parts%20set%20aside%20for%20forest%20produce%20extraction%20and%20tourism.%20In%20Bangladesh%2C%20there%20are%20three%20small%20sanctuaries%20which%20act%20as%20wildlife%20%E2%80%98hotspots%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20forest%20is%20open%20to%20harvesting%20of%20forest%20produce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%5BA%5D%20possible%20conduit%20for%20the%20tigers%20towards%20%5Bthe%5D%20east%20would%20be%20the%20channels%20which%20are%20less%20than%20400m%20wide%20and%20situated%20at%20the%20northern%20part%20of%20Basirhat%20range%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20continues%20to%20say%20that%20cooperation%20between%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%20will%20be%20necessary%20to%20protect%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20ecology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTrans-boundary%20cooperation%20and%20knowledge%20sharing%20between%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%20are%20important%20to%20maintain%20ecological%20integrity%20of%20the%20landscape.%20There%20is%20a%20need%20to%20explore%20areas%20within%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%20for%20tiger%20relocation%20as%20well%20as%20prey%20augmentation%2C%20as%20the%20population%20is%20nearing%20%5Bthe%5D%20carrying%20capacity%20of%20current%20prey%20density.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Flatest-census-data-insufficient-to-draw-any-conclusions-on-tiger-numbers-say-experts%5C%22%3ELatest%20Census%20Data%20%E2%80%98Insufficient%E2%80%99%20to%20Draw%20Any%20Conclusions%20on%20Tiger%20Numbers%2C%20Say%20Experts%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20Sundarban%20Tiger%20Reserve%20is%20home%20to%20a%20high%20number%20of%20tigers%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EDown%20to%20Earth%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fwildlife-biodiversity%2Fsundarbans-has-been-slipping-in-rank-despite-an-increased-tiger-count-here-s-why-88777%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20its%20ranking%20among%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20tiger%20reserves%20has%20fallen%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Sundarban%20reserve%20has%20done%20well%20in%20containing%20poaching%20and%20tiger-human%20conflict%2C%20staff%20shortage%20still%20remains%20a%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20leader%20of%20a%20different%20report%20the%20NTCA%20and%20WII%20prepared%20last%20year%20also%20emphasised%20the%20need%20for%20more%20staff%20and%20trans-border%20cooperation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20most%20important%20thing%20is%20to%20improve%20the%20staff%20strength%2C%20which%20was%20about%2050%25%20when%20it%20was%20evaluated.%20The%20lack%20of%20enough%20staff%20is%20affecting%20many%20areas%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3Cem%3EDown%20to%20Earth%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CMoreover%2C%20area%20development%20committees%20need%20to%20become%20functional%20under%20divisional%20commissioners%20to%20monitor%20illegal%20tourism.%20Over%20and%20above%2C%20more%20management%20coordination%20is%20required%20between%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%20Sundarbans%20forest%20areas.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDown%20to%20Earth%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20spoke%20to%20officials%20working%20in%20the%20Sundarban%20reserve%2C%20who%20said%20that%20efforts%20were%20on%20to%20increase%20the%20size%20of%20the%20reserve%2C%20which%20would%20ultimately%20result%20in%20staff%20receiving%20stronger%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691665556000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22htt