.com%2Ftapestry-coach-owner-acquires-capri-holdings-versace-michael-kors-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691665323000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d4a5bf4dd2b50019c28d9d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftapestry-coach-owner-acquires-capri-holdings-versace-michael-kors-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20new%20deal%20represents%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20acquisitions%20in%20the%20fashion%20industry%20in%20recent%20years%20and%20could%20bolster%20Tapestry's%20growth%20internationally.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Mary%20Hanbury)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftapestry-coach-owner-acquires-capri-holdings-versace-michael-kors-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UK%20Teacher%20Uses%20Dark%20Web%20To%20Pay%20Teens%20In%20India%20To%20Sexually%20Abuse%20Children%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20former%20deputy%20head%20teacher%20at%20a%20London%20primary%20school%20who%20had%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20paying%20and%20instructing%20teenagers%20in%20India%20to%20abuse%20younger%20children%20was%20sentenced%20to%2012%20years%20in%20prison%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMatthew%20Smith%2C%2035%2C%20from%20East%20Dulwich%20in%20south%20London%20was%20arrested%20by%20the%20UK's%20National%20Crime%20Agency%20(NCA)%20in%20November%20last%20year%20after%20its%20investigators%20identified%20that%20he%20was%20sharing%20abuse%20material%20on%20the%20dark%20web%20and%20has%20now%20been%20sentenced%20at%20Southwark%20Crown%20Court%20in%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20NCA%2C%20Smith%20was%20online%20at%20the%20time%20of%20his%20arrest%2C%20speaking%20to%20a%20teenage%20boy%20living%20in%20India%20and%20asking%20him%20to%20send%20sexual%20images%20of%20a%20younger%20child%2C%20in%20return%20for%20money.%20He%20also%20had%20dark%20web%20sites%20and%20forums%20open%20on%20his%20computer%20which%20were%20dedicated%20to%20child%20sexual%20abuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMatthew%20Smith%20is%20a%20prolific%20offender%20and%20master%20manipulator%2C%20who%20coerced%20young%20men%20into%20abusing%20children%20on%20his%20behalf%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Helen%20Dore%2C%20Senior%20Officer%20of%20the%20NCA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20constantly%20sought%20out%20opportunities%20to%20gain%20access%20to%20children%2C%20but%20was%20adept%20at%20hiding%20his%20sexual%20interest%20in%20them.%20He%20conducted%20his%20offending%20while%20working%20as%20a%20teacher%20and%20head%20of%20pastoral%20care%20-%20a%20deep%20betrayal%20of%20the%20trust%20placed%20in%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20clear%20Smith%20has%20absolutely%20no%20empathy%20for%20his%20victims%20and%20the%20harm%20he%20has%20caused%20them.%20He%20presents%20a%20very%20real%20and%20significant%20risk%20to%20children%2C%20but%20this%20investigation%20has%20ensured%20he%20will%20spend%20a%20long%20time%20in%20prison%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESmith%20is%20also%20subject%20to%20an%20indefinite%20sexual%20harm%20prevention%20order%20and%20has%20been%20placed%20on%20the%20sex%20offenders%20register%20for%20life.%20The%20NCA%20stressed%20that%20it%20is%20committed%20to%20operating%20online%20and%20overseas%2C%20working%20with%20global%20partners%20to%20ensure%20that%20children%20are%20safeguarded%20and%20offenders%20like%20Smith%20are%20brought%20to%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agency's%20investigators%20interrogated%20chat%20logs%20and%20financial%20transactions%20and%20were%20able%20to%20establish%20that%20Smith%20had%20paid%20that%20same%20teenager%2C%20and%20another%20also%20based%20in%20India%2C%20a%20total%20of%20GBP%2065%2C398%20to%20abuse%20children%20over%20a%20five-year%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chat%20logs%20showed%20that%20Smith%20would%20instruct%20the%20young%20men%20to%20perform%20sexual%20acts%20on%20boys%20and%20would%20send%20them%20images%20and%20videos%20as%20examples%20of%20ones%20he%20would%20like%20to%20receive%20in%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESmith%20also%20gave%20one%20of%20them%20advice%20on%20how%20to%20befriend%20children%20and%20build%20their%20trust%20with%20a%20view%20to%20abusing%20them.%20He%20had%20spent%20various%20periods%20working%20in%20orphanages%20and%20NGOs%20across%20India%20between%202007-2014%20and%20was%20later%20living%20in%20Nepal%20and%20working%20at%20a%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UK%20investigators%20found%20evidence%20of%20potential%20offending%20by%20Smith%20against%20children%20while%20he%20was%20working%20in%20India.%20The%20NCA%20shared%20information%20with%20the%20Indian%20authorities%20and%20said%20it%20continues%20to%20work%20with%20them%20in%20order%20to%20identify%20and%20safeguard%20victims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESmith%20moved%20back%20to%20the%20UK%20in%20July%202022%20and%20began%20working%20at%20a%20primary%20school%20in%20London%20in%20September%20that%20year%2C%20where%20he%20was%20a%20deputy%20head%20teacher%20and%20head%20of%20pastoral%20care.%20He%20was%20found%20to%20have%20posted%20an%20online%20advert%20at%20the%20time%20looking%20to%20secure%20a%20flat-share%2C%20in%20which%20he%20said%20he%20was%20a%20primary%20school%20teacher%20and%20could%20assist%20with%20childcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20arrested%20before%20he%20could%20be%20taken%20up%20on%20his%20offer%2C%20the%20NCA%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20there%20is%20no%20evidence%20to%20suggest%20he%20committed%20offences%20against%20children%20based%20in%20Nepal%20or%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficers%20recovered%20over%20120%2C000%20indecent%20images%20of%20children%2C%20which%20Smith%20had%20saved%20on%20a%20laptop%2C%20SD%20card%20and%20on%20his%20phone.%20In%20June%2C%20the%20NCA%20reported%20that%20he%20had%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20an%20initial%20five%20offences%2C%20including%20causing%20