%20storytelling%20still%20makes%20for%20addictive%20viewing.%20Among%20the%20issues%20are%20a%20bride%20obsessing%20about%20her%20complexion%3B%20a%20bride%20dealing%20with%20physical%20abuse%3B%20an%20inter-caste%20marriage%3B%20and%20a%20same-sex%20couple%20exchanging%20vows.%20Even%20though%20most%20of%20these%20issues%20keep%20coming%20up%20at%20weddings%20like%20clockwork%2C%20no%20one%20at%20the%20Made%20in%20Heaven%20offices%20seems%20to%20be%20batting%20an%20eyelid.%20No%20one%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20complaining%20though%2C%20given%20how%20watchable%20(and%20bingeable)%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMade%20In%20Heaven%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20show%20brings%20two%20new%20characters%20on%20board%20with%20its%20recurring%20ensemble%20of%20actors%20like%20Jim%20Sarbh%2C%20Kalki%20Koechlin%2C%20Shashank%20Arora%20and%20Shivani%20Raghuvanshi.%20TV%20star%20Mona%20Singh%20plays%20Bulbul%20Jauhari%2C%20wife%20of%20Mr%20Jauhari%20(the%20always-excellent%20Vijay%20Raaz)%20joins%20the%20office%20as%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eauditor%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eoversee%20expenses%2C%20so%20as%20to%20turn%20Made%20In%20Heaven%20into%20a%20profit-making%20organisation.%20Singh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20career%20trajectory%20has%20been%20interesting%20since%20she%20moved%20away%20from%20TV%2C%20doing%20bit%20roles%20in%20mainstream%20films%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E3%20Idiots%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2008)%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELaal%20Singh%20Chaddha%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20in%20which%20she%20was%20the%20best%20thing.%20She%E2%80%99s%20also%20excellent%20in%20the%20new%20season.%20Raising%20a%20teenage%20boy%20who%20is%20accused%20of%20molesting%20a%20fellow%20classmate%2C%20Singh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20face%20conveys%20what%20millions%20of%20words%20couldn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Et.%20The%20fear%20that%20her%20son%20is%20carrying%20his%20biological%20father%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20DNA%2C%20the%20disgust%20when%20she%20knows%20he%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20lying%20through%20his%20teeth%2C%20the%20perplexed%20look%20when%20the%20other%20parents%20casually%20slut-shame%20the%20girl%20%E2%80%93%20Singh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20eyes%20are%20a%20horror%20film%20here.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETrinetra%20Haldar%2C%20a%20trans%20actor%2C%20plays%20Meher%20Chaudhary%20%E2%80%93%20the%20new%20head%20of%20production%20at%20the%20wedding-planning%20company.%20Even%20though%20we%20should%20laud%20the%20intent%20of%20showrunners%2C%20the%20character%20isn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Et%20as%20incidental%20as%20they%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ed%20like%20it%20to%20be.%20Over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20show%2C%20Meher%20becomes%20a%20vessel%20for%20trans%20sensitisation%2C%20a%20noble%20thought%2C%20but%20without%20ever%20becoming%20a%20fully%20fleshed-out%2C%20flawed%20person%20of%20her%20own.%20Those%20who%20have%20seen%20Saim%20Sadiq%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJoyland%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2022)%2C%20which%20employs%20a%20trans%20character%20in%20a%20subversive%20manner%2C%20might%20be%20able%20to%20see%20how%20Haldar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20character%20never%20reaches%20beyond%20its%20place-holder%20status.%20It%20wouldn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Et%20be%20unfair%20to%20expect%20a%20bit%20more%20nuance%20from%20directors%20as%20socially%20cognisant%20as%20Akhtar%2C%20Kagti%2C%20Ghaywan%20and%20Shrivastava%2C%20would%20it%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMade%20In%20Heaven%202%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20some%20clever%20special%20appearances%20like%20Sanjay%20Kapoor%20playing%20a%20jovial%2C%20greedy%20bred-in-Delhi%20boomer%2C%20who%20cracks%20silly%20jokes%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EBaraatiyon%20ka%20swaagat%20single%20malt%20se%20kiya%20jaaye%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20then%20leans%20in%20to%20hi-five%20everyone%20in%20his%20vicinity.%20Unfortunately%2C%20it%20barely%20registers%20in%20one%20of%20the%20weakest%20episodes%20of%20the%20show%2C%20despite%20a%20crackling%20premise.%20Anurag%20Kashyap%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20wink-at-the-audience%20performances%20are%20slowly%20becoming%20too%20boring%20and%20one-note.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERadhika%20Apte%20is%20a%20pleasure%20to%20watch%20as%20an%20Ivy%20League%20scholar%2C%20who%20despite%20having%20the%20world%20at%20her%20feet%2C%20is%20reduced%20to%20her%20Dalit%20surname%20in%20her%20own%20wedding.%20In%20a%20show%20where%20each%20episode%20feels%20like%20a%20refresher%20course%20in%20a%20new%20social%20justice%20issue%2C%20Apte%20brings%20a%20real%20vulnerability%20to%20her%20character.%20Playing%20a%20scholar%20from%20a%20Dalit%20community%2C%20she%20grapples%20with%20her%20politics%20and%20being%20affable%20with%20her%20future%20in-laws%2C%20between%20flashes%20of%20self-importance%20and%20carrying%20around%20the%20weight%20of%20her%20ideology.%20Without%20Apte%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20deeply-moving%20performance%2C%20the%20episode%20could%20have%20easily%20become%20a%20Doordarshan%20PSA.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20second%20season%20carries%20forward%20some%20ghosts%20from%20the%20first%20%E2%80%93%20like%20Kabir%20Basrai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20(Shashank%20Arora)%20insufferable%2C%20condescending%20voiceover.%20Frankly%2C%20it%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20shocking%20that%20Kagti%20and%20Akhtar%20have%20persisted%20with%20his%20platitudes%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eexplaining%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhat%20just%20happened%20in%20the%20episode%2C%20seemingly%20written%20by%20a%20slam-poet%20from%20GK-II.%20Arora%20is%20excellent%20when%20he%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20just%20being%20his%20loose%20self%20on%20screen%2C%20especially%20around%20Raghuvanshi%20%E2%80%93%20arguably%20the%20most%20spontaneous%20actor%20in%20this%20solid%20ensemble.%20Jim%20Sarbh%20is%20pitch-perfect%20in%20a%20scene%20at%20the%20divorce%20court%2C%20where%20he%20snootily%20compares%20coffee%20to%20dishwater.%20There%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20just%20the%20right%20amount%20of%20privilege%2C%20entitlement%2C%20and%20civility%20to%20make%20Adil%20seem%20like%20a%20fully-rounded%20character%20%E2%80%93%20instead%20of%20an%20easy-to-dislike%20rich%20brat.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMade%20in%20Heaven%202%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ebelongs%20to%20one%20character%20only%20%E2%80%93%20Sobhita%20Dhulipala%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20Tara.%20It%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20possibly%20the%20most%20compelling%20lead%20character%20written%20in%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20OTT%20era%20(spanning%20almost%20six%20years%20now).%20The%20show%20fully%20embraces%20Tara%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20twisted%2C%20selfish%20ways%20%E2%80%93%20painting%20her%20as%20a%20loyal%20friend%2C%20a%20dutiful%20daughter%20and%20daughter-in-law%3B%20an%20outsider%20desperately%20trying%20to%20find%20her%20way%20in%2C%20disillusioned%20by%20how%20