olicy-august-2023-8885226%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20key%20policy%20rate%20has%20remained%20unchanged%20for%20three%20cycles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%20Governor%20Shaktikanta%20Das%20said%20that%20the%20six-member%20monetary%20policy%20committee%20(MPC)%20unanimously%20decided%20to%20keep%20the%20lending%20rate%20at%206.50%25.%20The%20MPC%20also%20retained%20its%20withdrawal%20of%20accommodation%20stance%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20retail%20inflation%20remains%20within%20the%20targeted%204%25.%20Withdrawal%20of%20accommodative%20stance%20means%20reducing%20the%20money%20supply%20in%20the%20system%20to%20rein%20in%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20central%20bank%E2%80%99s%20policy%20committee%20had%20hiked%20the%20repo%20rate%20by%20250%20basis%20points%20from%20May%202022%20to%20February%202023.%20Das%20said%20that%20the%20headline%20inflation%20after%20reaching%20a%20low%20of%204.3%25%20in%20May%202023%2C%20rose%20in%20June%20and%20is%20expected%20to%20surge%20during%20July%20and%20August%2C%20owing%20to%20the%20rise%20in%20vegetable%20prices%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20RBI%20has%20projected%20India%E2%80%99s%20Q2%20retail%20inflation%20at%206.2%25%3B%20Q3%20at%205.7%25%20and%20Q4%20at%205.2%25%20in%20the%20current%20fiscal%20year%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDas%20said%20that%20the%20consumer%20price%20index%20(CPI)%20inflation%20forecast%20for%20FY2023-24%20has%20been%20raised%20to%205.4%25%20from%205.1%25%20due%20to%20the%20rise%20in%20vegetable%20prices%2C%20while%20the%20gross%20domestic%20product%20(GDP)%20forecast%20has%20been%20retained%20at%206.5%25%2C%20with%20risks%20evenly%20balanced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20vegetable%20price%20shock%20may%20reverse%20quickly%2C%20possible%20El%20Nino%20weather%20conditions%2C%20along%20with%20global%20food%20prices%20need%20to%20be%20watched%20closely%2C%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20a%20skewed%20Southwest%20Monsoon%2C%E2%80%9D%20Das%20was%20quoted%20by%20the%20paper%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20developments%20warrant%20a%20heightened%20vigil%20on%20the%20evolving%20inflation%20trajectory%2C%E2%80%9D%20Das%20cautioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20cumulative%20rate%20hike%20of%20250%20basis%20points%2C%20undertaken%20by%20the%20MPC%20so%20far%2C%20is%20working%20its%20way%20into%20the%20economy.%20Nevertheless%2C%20domestic%20economic%20activity%20is%20holding%20up%20well%2C%20and%20is%20likely%20to%20retain%20its%20momentum%2C%20despite%2C%20weak%20external%20demand.%20Considering%20this%20confluence%20of%20factors%2C%20the%20MPC%20decided%20to%20remain%20watchful%20and%20evaluate%20the%20emerging%20situation%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDas%20reaffirmed%20that%20the%20MPC%20is%20resolute%20in%20its%20commitment%20to%20%E2%80%9Calign%20inflation%20to%20the%204%25%20target%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Canchoring%20inflation%20expectations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20RBI%20also%20asked%20banks%20to%20set%20aside%20a%20larger%20part%20of%20incremental%20deposits%20to%20tighten%20liquidity.%20With%20effect%20from%20the%20August%2012%20fortnight%2C%20banks%20shall%20maintain%20an%20incremental%20cash%20reserve%20ratio%20of%2010%25%20on%20increase%20in%20deposits%20between%20May%2019%20and%20July%2028%2C%20Das%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691655142000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F10133610%2FShaktikanta_Das_IAS.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Frepo-rate-unchanged-at-6-50-committed-to-limit-inflation-at-4-rbi-gov%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20RBI%20has%20projected%20India%E2%80%99s%20Q2%20retail%20inflation%20at%206.2%25%3B%20Q3%20at%205.7%25%20and%20Q4%20at%205.2%25%20in%20the%20current%20fiscal%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Frepo-rate