%20of%20interest%3A%20EG.5.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormerly%20a%20variant%20under%20monitoring%2C%20WHO%20has%20now%20designated%20this%20a%20variant%20of%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20a%20steady%20increase%20in%20this%20variant%E2%80%99s%20prevalence.%20As%20of%207%20August%202023%2C%20over%207000%20sequences%20have%20been%20shared%20from%2051%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FDlDdAPYMos%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FDlDdAPYMos%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(WHO)%20(%40WHO)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FWHO%2Fstatus%2F1689296350804901889%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%209%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20else%20do%20we%20know%20about%20the%20EG.5%20variant%20of%20COVID-19%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20WHO%20said%20that%20the%20new%20variant%20does%20not%20at%20present%20seem%20to%20pose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Frepeated-covid-19-infection-increases-health-risks-new-study-shows%2Fa-63714302%5C%22%3Ean%20additional%20public%20health%20risk%20compared%20to%20other%20strains%20of%20COVID-19%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCollectively%2C%20available%20evidence%20does%20not%20suggest%20that%20EG.5%20has%20additional%20public%20health%20risks%20relative%20to%20the%20other%20currently%20circulating%20Omicron%20descendent%20lineages%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20organisation%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20a%20more%20comprehensive%20evaluation%20of%20the%20risk%20posed%20by%20EG.5%20was%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20WHO%20defines%20a%20%E2%80%98variant%20of%20interest%E2%80%99%20as%20one%20which%20likely%20has%20growth%20advantage%20over%20circulating%20variants%20and%20can%20enhance%20the%20transmissibility%20of%20the%20virus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20of%20greater%20significance%20and%20rather%20alarm%20is%20a%20Variant%20of%20Concern.%20Omicron%20was%20the%20last%20declared%20VoC%20of%20the%20novel%20coronavirus.%20A%20variant%20is%20declared%20of%20concern%20if%20it%20causes%20a%20change%20in%20disease%20severity%2C%20or%20substantial%20impact%20on%20healthcare%20systems%20or%20a%20significant%20decrease%20in%20the%20ability%20of%20vaccines%20to%20prevent%20the%20infection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaria%20Van%20Kerkhove%2C%20the%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20technical%20lead%20on%20COVID-19%2C%20said%20that%20while%20EG.5%20had%20increased%20transmissibility%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fxbb15-likely-to-be-the-next-major-covid-subvariant%2Fa-64292961%5C%22%3Einfections%20were%20not%20more%20severe%20than%20other%20Omicron%20variants%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20don%E2%80%99t%20detect%20a%20change%20in%20severity%20of%20EG.5%20compared%20to%20other%20sublineages%20of%20Omicron%20that%20have%20been%20in%20circulation%20since%20late%202021%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Dr%20Mandy%20Cohen%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20US%20Center%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20(CDC)%2C%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fnew-mrna-vaccine-hub-officially-launched-in-cape-town%2Fa-65383690%5C%22%3Eupdated%20vaccines%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20offered%20in%20mid-to-late%20September%20will%20provide%20protection%20against%20the%20variant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRight%20now%2C%20what%20we%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20with%20the%20changes%20in%20the%20viruses%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20still%20susceptible%20to%20our%20vaccine%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20still%20susceptible%20to%20our%20medicines%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20still%20picked%20up%20by%20the%20tests%2C%E2%80%9D%20Cohen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CDC%20chief%20said%20that%20the%20mutations%20in%C2%A0the%20virus%20amounted%20to%20%E2%80%9Csmall%20changes%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Csubtypes%20of%20what%20we%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20before.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20likely%20to%20see%20this%20as%20a%20recommendation%20as%20an%20annual%20COVID%20shot%20just%20like%20we%20have%20an%20annual%20flu%20shot%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECountries%20not%20reporting%20COVID-19%20data%2C%20WHO%20says%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20WHO%20director%20general%20Tedros%20Adhanom%20Ghebreyesus%20said%20that%20many%20countries%20were%20not%20reporting%20coronavirus%20data%20to%20the%20organisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20only%2011%25%20had%20reported%20hospitalisations%20and%20ICU%20admissions%20related%20to%20COVID-19.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20WHO%20issued%20a%20set%20of%20recommendations%20for%20reporting%20data%20on%20the%20virus%2C%20particularly%20mortality%20and%20morbidity.%20It%20also%20urged%20countries%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fcoronavirus-vaccine%2Ft-55769446%5C%22%3Econtinue%20offering%20vaccination%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAbout%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20we%20were%20in%20a%20much%20better%20situation%20to%20either%20anticipate%20or%20act%20or%20be%20more%20agile%2C%E2%80%9D%20Van%20Kerkhove%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnd%20now%20the%20delay%20in%20our%20ability%20to%20do%20that%20is%20growing.%20And%20our%20ability%20to%20do%20this%20is%20declining.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20we%20cannot%20do%20right%20now%20is%20give%20you%20an%20accurate%20statistic%20of%20how%20many%20deaths%20are%20actually%20occurring%20for%20COVID-19%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20on%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftop-stories%2Fs-9097%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flogs1279.xiti.com%2Fhit.xiti%3Fs%3D531599%26s2%3D2%26p