Fmsid-102588678%2Cimgsize-28772.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fmumbai%2Fmaharashtra-reports-first-covid-19-death-in-mnths%2Farticleshow%2F102588659.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20state%20government%20reported%20a%20Covid-19%20death%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20marking%20the%20first%20fatality%20in%20months.%20This%20death%2C%20however%2C%20did%20not%20occur%20recently%3B%20it%20took%20place%20in%20July%2C%20as%20stated%20by%20the%20BMC.%20The%20inclusion%20of%20this%20death%20in%20the%20official%20records%20happened%20just%20this%20Wednesday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TNN%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sheikh%20Abdullah%20in%201968%3A%20'Accession%20Is%20of%20Minds%2C%20Hearts%3B%20Love%20%26%20Justice%20Are%20the%20Only%20Weapons%20You%20Need'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F03%2F15160532%2FBeFunky-collage-4.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20interview%20with%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%20was%20first%20published%20in%20the%20February%201968%20edition%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Weekend%20Review%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20supplement%20published%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20Wire%20is%20republishing%20it%20now%20because%20of%20the%20bearing%20it%20has%20on%20the%20ongoing%20debates%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20elsewhere%20over%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20constitutional%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIt%20is%20February%2C%201968.%20In%20a%20bungalow%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20the%20Lion%20of%20Kashmir%20Sheikh%20Mohammed%20Abdullah%20waits%20for%20the%20weather%20to%20moderate%20and%20the%20road%20to%20open%20so%20that%20he%20may%20return%20to%20his%20homeland.%20He%20waits%20also%2C%20with%20dwindling%20hope%20and%20increasing%20despondency%2C%20for%20some%20sign%20from%20the%20Union%20government%20that%20it%20is%20willing%20to%20give%20up%20its%20ostrich%20attitude%20on%20Kashmir.%20Today%20history%20is%20threatening%20to%20repeat%20itself.%20A%20carefully%20planned%20campaign%20seems%20to%20have%20been%20launched%20to%20rouse%20communal%20violence%20and%20then%20point%20to%20him%20as%20its%20cause.%20He%20has%20been%20falsely%20accused%20of%20having%20met%20the%20Chinese%20Charge%20d%E2%80%99%20Affaires%20in%20the%20Pakistan%20High%20Commission.%20The%20ground%20is%20thus%20being%20prepared%20to%20force%20the%20government%20to%20put%20him%20away%20again%20as%20it%20did%20in%201963%2C%20in%201958%2C%20and%20in%201965.%20The%20Sheikh%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Csin%E2%80%9D%20is%20that%20he%20is%20an%20uncompromising%20idealist%20in%20an%20era%20of%20political%20disillusionment.%20In%20this%20interview%20with%20Prem%20Shankar%20%C2%A0Jha%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3EWeekend%20Review%3Cem%3E%2C%20he%20sets%20out%20the%20political%20convictions%20that%20have%20sustained%20him%20in%20his%20long%20travail.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20were%20you%20first%20attracted%20to%20politics%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20what%20I%20saw%20around%20me%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20I%20think%2C%20that%20first%20attracted%20me%20to%20politics%20%E2%80%93%20the%20distress%2C%20and%20the%20poverty%20which%20I%20saw%20as%20I%20grew%20up.%20As%20I%20have%20been%20telling%20my%20friends%20here%20(in%20Delhi)%2C%20Kashmir%2C%20because%20of%20its%20natural%20beauty%2C%20has%20always%20attracted%20conquerors%20who%20have%20treated%20it%20as%20a%20prize%20a%20luxury%20item%20made%20simply%20for%20their%20enjoyment.%20They%20never%20thought%20of%20the%20Kashmiri%20people.%20This%20has%20been%20true%20of%20all%20conquerors%20including%20the%20Moghuls%20and%20most%20recently%20the%20Dogras.%20During%20all%20this%20time%2C%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20people%20were%20seldom%20looked%20after%2C%20and%20as%20I%20grew%20I%20found%20that%20poverty%20and%20illiteracy%20prevailed%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20led%20you%20to%20convert%20the%20Kashmir%20Muslim%20Conference%20into%20the%20National%20Conference%20in%201938%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20see%2C%20I%20was%20brought%20up%20in%20a%20place%20where%20I%20had%20the%20people%20of%20one%20community%20all%20around%20me%2C%20that%20is%20Muslims.%20Generally%20the%20Muslims%20are%20very%20much%20downtrodden%20in%20Kashmir.%20They%20are%20a%20huge%20majority%20%E2%80%93%2095%25.%20So%20naturally%20my%20first%20contact%20was%20with%20them%20and%20I%20was%20influenced%20by%20their%20distress%20and%20the%20injustices%20they%20suffered%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20officialdom.%20So%20I%20had%20the%20idea%20that%20they%20were%20suffering%20on%20account%20of%20their%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20later%20when%20I%20had%20had%20an%20opportunity%20to%20travel%20around%20and%20tour%20the%20whole%20state%2C%20I%20came%20across%20other%20people%20belonging%20to%20other%20religious%20communities%20%E2%80%93%20Hindus%20and%20Sikhs%20%E2%80%93%20receiving%20the%20same%2C%20and%20in%20places%20even%20worse%2C%20treatment%20than%20Muslims.%20So%20I%20came%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20the%20real%20fight%20was%20not%20between%20two%20religions%2C%20or%20two%20religious%20groups%2C%20but%20between%20%E2%80%9Chaves%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Chave%20nots%E2%80%9D%2C%20oppressed%20and%20oppressor.%20I%20found%20there%20were%20Muslims%2C%20there%20were%20Sikhs%20%E2%80%93%20people%20of%20all%20communities.%20So%20I%20began%20to%20feel%20that%20if%20one%E2%80%99s%20real%20purpose%20was%20to%20relieve%20oppression%20or%20distress%2C%20the%20best%20course%20was%20to%20serve%20not%20one%20group%20but%20all%20the%20people%20irrespective%20of%20caste%2C%20creed%20or%20colour.%20That%20was%20my%20reason%20for%20broad-basing%20the%20old%20Muslim%20Conference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWas%20it%20when%20you%20found%20that%20the%20condition%20of%20oppression%20was%20not%20merely%20confined%20to%20Kashmir%20that%20you%20decided%20to%20join%20the%20States%E2%80%99%20People%E2%80%99s%20Conference%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20initially%20of%20course%20my%20views%20were%20formed%20by%20touring%20Kashmir%20state%2C%20but%20later%20when%20I%20went%20to%20Hyderabad%2C%20for%20example%2C%20I%20found%20the%20overwhelmingly%20Hindu%20population%20of%20that%20state%20in%20the%20same%20condition%20as%20the%20population%20of%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20did%20you%20meet%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20and%20Pandit%20Nehru%2C%20and%20what%20impression%20or%20impact%20did%20they%20create%20on%20you%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20met%20Panditji%20first%20when%20he%20visited%20Lahore%20and%20he%20was%20staying%20with%20Mian%20Iftikhar-ud-din%20Khan.%20I%20met%20him%20not%20at%20his%20house%20but%20at%20the%20railway%20station%20when%20he%20was%20proceeding%20to%20the%20(North%20West)%20frontier.%20It%20was%201938%20or%201939.%20We%20had%20a%20talk%20at%20the%20railway%20station%E2%80%A6%20I%20sat%20in%20his%20compartment%E2%80%A6and%20accompanied%20him%20on%20his%20tour.%20Just%20like%20that.%20Just%20like%20that%20we%20had%20a%20long%20exchange%20of%20ideas.%20That%20was%20my%20first%20contact%20with%20him.%20At%20that%20time%20we%20discussed%20how%20to%20open%20the%20gates%20of%20the%20Muslim%20Conference%20to%20the%20other%20minorities%20in%20the%20state%20in%20Kashmir.%20We%20did%20not%20have%20to%20do%20(much)%20because%20the%20basic%20principles%20of%20the%20Muslim%20Conference%20were%20already%20universal%20and%20non-communal.%20So%20we%20had%20only%20to%20discuss%20the%20technical%20part%20of%20how%20to%20do%20it.%20We%20exchanged%20our%20ideas.%20I%20told%20him%20of%20my%20difficulties%20and%20he%20discussed%20the%20advantages%20of%20broad-basing%20the%20movement.%20So%20that%20was%20my%20first%20contact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGandhi%E2%80%99s%20impact%20on%20me%20was%20that%20he%20was%20a%20man%20of%20high%20principles%20and%20of%20noble%2C%20political%20ideals.%20He%20had%20a%20religious%20bent%20of%20mind.%20This%20attracted%20me%20to%20him%20ideologically.%20Another%20thing%20which%20impressed%20me%20was%20that%20he%20was%20a%20lover%20of%20truth.%20He%20would%20always%20stand%20by%20the%20truth.%20Once%20he%20was%20convinced%20that%20a%20certain%20thing%20was%20wrong%20it%20would%20not%20take%20him%20a%20minute%20to%20admit%20it.%20In%20his%20whole%20life%20he%20would%20not%20ask%20others%20to%20do%20anything%20which%20he%20himself%20would%20not%20practice%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201945-46%20Mr%20Jinnah%20came%20to%20Kashmir.%20What%20he%20was%20seeking%20at%20that%20time%20was%20to%20reconvert%20the%20National%20Conference%20into%20the%20Muslim%20Conference.%20Therein%20we%20naturally%20did%20not%20agree.%20But%20in%20Delhi%20when%20I%20met%20him%20I%20told%20him%20it%20was%20not%20my%20view%20only%20which%20matters%2C%20and%20that%20I%20would%20ask%20the%20advice%20of%20my%20colleagues.%20%5BI%20explained%20to%20him%20that%5D%20in%201931-32%2C%20we%20had%20gone%20through%20this%20debate%20and%20come%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20it%20was%20not%20merely%20a%20question%20of%20communities%2C%20and%20that%20it%20was%20the%20duty%20of%20every%20Muslim%20to%20fight%20to%20relieve%20the%20distress%20of%20everyone.%20We%20believed%20that%20this%20was%20the%20true%20Islam%2C%20so%20the%20Muslim%20Conference%20was%20opened%20to%20minorities.%20Unless%20I%20was%20convinced%20that%20this%20was%20wrong%2C%20I%20could%20not%20go%20back%20on%20this%20decision.%20I%20said%20that%20if%20my%20other%20colleagues%20decided%20unanimously%20to%20back%20to%20the%20original%20position%2C%20then%20I%20would%20not%20stand%20in%20the%20way.%20But%20in%20that%20case%20I%20would%20not%20be%20able%20to%20lead%20the%20Conference%20because%20personally%20I%20would%20still%20not%20be%20convinced.%20But%20I%20would%20accept%20the%20decision%20of%20my%20party%20because%20as%20a%20democratic%20principal%20if%20the%20majority%20decides%2C%20naturally%20I%20would%20then%20have%20to%20either%20follow%20or%20quit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20finally%20no%20decision%20was%20needed.%20Mr%20Jinnah%20had%20come%20to%20Kashmir.%20He%20had%20accepted%20my%20decision.%20But%20there%20probably%2C%20he%20was%20advised%20not%20to%20accept%20my%20proposal%20to%20put%20his%20suggestion%20to%20the%20Conference%20because%20it%20was%20felt%20that%20I%20had%20so%20much%20influence%20with%20the%20working%20of%20the%20National%20Conference%20that%20they%20would%20always%20go%20by%20my%20advice.%20So%20he%20avoided%20referring%20the%20matter%20to%20the%20Conference.%20Naturally%20there%20was%20a%20conflict%20apparently%20after%20that%20his%20position%20was%20changed%20and%20he%20supported%20the%20Maharaja.%20His%20position%20as%20far%20as%20the%20princes%20were%20concerned%20was%20that%20the%20right%20to%20%E2%80%98decide%20the%20future%E2%80%99%20affiliation%20was%20given%20to%20the%20princes%20and%20not%20the%20people.%20Therefore%20he%20stuck%20to%20that%20position%2C%20whilst%20the%20Indian%20Congress%20and%20the%20State%20Peoples%20Conference%20opposed%20his%20view%20point.%20They%20said%20that%20it%20was%20the%20right%20of%20the%20people%20to%20decide%2C%20and%20not%20of%20one%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07143637%2F1024px-Sheikh_Abdullah_addressing_people.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07143637%2F1024px-Sheikh_Abdullah_addressing_people.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07143637%2F1024px-Sheikh_Abdullah_addressing_people-300x218.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666977%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22743%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESheikh%20Abdullah%20addressing%20a%20gathering%20at%20Lal%20Chowk%20in%20Srinagar%20in%201975.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20was%20the%20situation%20in%20Kashmir%20in%201947%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20before%20the%20emergency%20in%201947%2C%20I%20found%20anxiety%20all%20round%2C%20because%20of%20what%20was%20happening%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20Punjab.%20Thousands%20of%20refugees%2C%20both%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%2C%20had%20poured%20into%20the%20state.%20%C2%A0They%20had%20suffered%20a%20lot%20and%20there%20was%20tension%20between%20the%20Hindus%20and%20Muslim%20of%20Kashmir.%20There%20was%20anxiety%20about%20what%20was%20going%20to%20happen.%20Then%20the%20Maharaja%20had%20not%20taken%20any%20decision%20about%20the%20accession.%20This%20was%20the%20main%20question%20that%20faced%20me%20on%20my%20release%20from%20jail%20on%20the%2028th%20of%20September%2C%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20my%20first%20public%20meeting%20which%20I%20addressed%20in%20Srinagar%2C%20I%20made%20my%20position%20on%20the%20accession%20clear.%20I%20felt%20that%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20were%20not%20in%20a%20position%20to%20take%20a%20decision%20at%20that%20moment%20because%20they%20did%20not%20know%20what%20shape%2C%20ultimately%2C%20the%20two%20dominions%20would%20take.%20There%20was%20so%20much%20trouble%20and%20nobody%20even%20knew%20whether%20the%20two%20dominions%20would%20exist.%20I%20suppose%20nobody%20knew%20whether%20the%20secular%20principle%20would%20survive%20at%20that%20time.%20Nobody%20knew%20what%20was%20going%20to%20happen.%20So%20we%20thought%20that%20this%20was%20not%20the%20time%20to%20take%20a%20decision%20which%20would%20influence%20not%20only%20us%20but%20also%20future%20generations.%20So%20we%20needed%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20one%20consideration.%20The%20second%20consideration%20was%20that%20we%20had%20been%20fighting%20since%201931%20for%20a%20responsible%20government%20in%20Kashmir.%20We%20had%20not%20achieved%20that%20objective%20and%20the%20Maharaja%20was%20still%20an%20autocrat.%20We%20had%20to%20first%20gain%20our%20freedom%20before%20deciding%20about%20accession%20and%20we%20requested%20the%20heads%20of%20both%20the%20dominions%2C%20both%20Congress%20and%20the%20Muslim%20League%2C%20not%20to%20force%20us%20to%20take%20a%20decision%20at%20that%20moment%2C%20but%20to%20leave%20us%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20sent%20one%20of%20my%20colleagues%20Mr%20G.M.%20Sadiq%2C%20who%20is%20the%20present%20chief%20minister%2C%20to%20Lahore%20to%20meet%20the%20prime%20minister%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20Mr%20Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan%20and%20to%20put%20this%20question%20before%20him%2C%20but%20unfortunately%20they%20took%20the%20position%20that%20as%20the%20subcontinent%20was%20divided%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20Muslims%20and%20Hindus%2C%20and%20as%20Kashmir%20was%20a%20Muslim-majority%20area%2C%20it%20must%20%3Cem%3Eipso%20facto%3C%2Fem%3E%20come%20to%20Pakistan.%20That%20position%20was%20not%20acceptable%20to%20us.%20Mr%20Sadiq%20told%20Pakistan%20that%20the%20decision%20must%20not%20be%20imposed%20on%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20but%20they%20should%20be%20given%20a%20chance%20to%20decide%20their%20own%20fate.%20Both%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20must%20accept%20(their)%20decision%2C%20whatever%20it%20may%20be.%20There%20was%20no%20agreement%20on%20that%2C%20so%20Sadiq%20returned%20and%2C%20soon%20after%2C%20the%20raids%20began%20and%20the%20picture%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20raids%20began%20the%20Maharaja%20could%20not%20stop%20them%20because%20his%20forces%20were%20spread%20out%20throughout%20the%20state%20in%20small%2C%20batches.%20The%20raiders%20therefore%20nearly%20reached%20Srinagar%2C%20so%20he%20was%20advised%20(I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20by%20whom)%20and%20left%20in%20the%20dead%20of%20the%20night%20with%20his%20personal%20staff%20and%20belongings%20for%20Jammu%3B%20meanwhile%20he%20requested%20India%20for%20military%20support.%20India%20could%20not%20give%20this%20military%20support%20unless%20some%20legal%20basis%20was%20established.%20Lord%20Mountbatten%20advised%20his%20colleagues%2C%20Pandit%20Nehru%20and%20others%20that%20it%20would%20be%20wrong%20for%20India%20to%20send%20troops%20into%20a%20technically%20independent%20state.%20If%20India%20did%20so%2C%20Pakistan%20would%20do%20the%20same%20and%20there%20would%20be%20a%20clash%20between%20the%20two%20dominions%2C%20and%20since%20the%20army%20was%20still%20controlled%20by%20British%20personnel%20on%20both%20sides%2C%20it%20would%20be%20difficult%20for%20them%20to%20fight.%20So%20he%20suggested%20that%20some%20legal%20formula%20should%20be%20established.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Maharaja%20was%20told%20that%20military%20help%20would%20come%20(legally)%20only%20if%20he%20signed%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession.%20Thus%20the%20Maharaja%20signed%20under%20duress%2C%20and%20in%20his%20letter%20whilst%20forwarding%20the%20document%20to%20Lord%20Mountbatten%20he%20stated%20clearly%20the%20circumstances%20under%20which%20he%20had%20signed%20the%20accession.%20Realising%20this%20position%20and%20the%20desire%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%20for%20self-determination%20and%20their%20refusal%20to%20give%20up%20that%20position%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20Pakistan%2C%20the%20leaders%20of%20India%20accepted%20the%20accession%20provisionally%20subject%20to%20ratification%20by%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20at%20a%20later%20stage%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20plebiscite.%20The%20condition%20of%20a%20plebiscite%20was%20laid%20%5Bdown%5D%20at%20that%20very%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWas%20it%20specifically%20plebiscite%2C%20or%20a%20%E2%80%98reference%20to%20the%20people%E2%80%99%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20that%20I%20would%20like%20you%20to%20see%20V.P.%20Menon%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Integration%20of%20the%20Indian%20States%3C%2Fem%3E.%20He%20has%20devoted%20a%20chapter%20to%20each%20state%20and%20there%20is%20one%20on%20Kashmir%20too.%20He%20clearly%20says%20that%20because%20of%20these%20considerations%20the%20accession%20was%20%E2%80%98accepted%20subject%20to%20a%20plebiscite%E2%80%99.%20He%20has%20clearly%20used%20the%20word%20plebiscite%20in%20his%20book.%20Actually%20it%20was%20Lord%20Mountbatten%20in%20his%20letter%20to%20the%20Maharaja%20in%20which%20he%20accepted%20the%20deed%20of%20accession%2C%20who%20said%20this%20would%20become%20final%20after%20a%20%E2%80%9Creference%20to%20the%20people%E2%80%9D%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20were%20the%20problems%20you%20faced%20during%20the%20emergency%20government%20when%20you%20became%20prime%20minster%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20problems%20were%20multifold.%20Firstly%20there%20was%20a%20fear%20complex%3A%20Muslims%20were%20afraid%20of%20Hindus%20and%20Hindus%20were%20afraid%20of%20Muslims.%20In%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20state%2C%20Hindus%20would%20not%20think%20of%20going%20to%20Pakistan%20because%20of%20what%20had%20happened%20on%20that%20side.%20They%20thought%20they%20would%20be%20completely%20finished%20if%20the%20state%20acceded%20to%20Pakistan.%20The%20Muslims%20were%20afraid%20that%20if%20the%20state%20joined%20India%20then%20their%20fate%20would%20be%20the%20same%20as%20of%20Muslims%20in%20Kapurthala%20and%20other%20Punjab%20states.%20In%20India%20too%2C%20at%20that%20time%2C%20there%20were%20definitely%20two%20trends.%20One%20was%20the%20secular%20concept%20and%20the%20other%20trend%20was%20towards%20a%20theocratic%20concept.%20The%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%20and%20parts%20of%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20general%20mass%20of%20the%20people%20also%20thought%20that%20if%20%E2%80%9Cthey%E2%80%9D%20have%20a%20Muslim%20state%20we%20must%20have%20a%20Hindu%20state.%20So%20(in%20Kashmir)%20we%20had%20to%20fight%20these%20trends.%20It%20was%20a%20tough%20fight%20and%20an%20uphill%20task%20for%20those%20who%20believed%20in%20humanity%20and%20not%20in%20Hindus%2C%20Muslims%20or%20Sikhs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20problem%20facing%20us%3A%20how%20to%20create%20confidence%20in%20the%20two%20sectors%20in%20Kashmir.%20I%20thought%20that%20remaining%20in%20India%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20was%20enough%20guarantee%20for%20the%20non-Muslims%20that%20their%20lives%20would%20be%20safeguarded%20and%20that%20their%20rights%20would%20be%20safeguarded.%20But%20how%20to%20create%20confidence%20amongst%20the%20Muslims.%20I%20thought%20that%20by%20guaranteeing%20an%20autonomous%20position%20(for)%20the%20state%2C%20they%20would%20have%20an%20assurance%20that%20there%20would%20be%20no%20interference%20with%20their%20internal%20affairs.%20As%20a%20majority%2C%20it%20would%20be%20up%20to%20them%20to%20provide%20safeguards%20for%20the%20minority%20and%20not%20vice%20versa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20this%2C%20they%20would%20have%20the%20tremendous%20advantage%20of%20being%20a%20part%20of%20a%20country%20which%20claimed%20to%20be%20democratic%20and%20progressive%2C%20and%20in%20which%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20prevailed.%20By%20remaining%20a%20part%20of%20such%20a%20state%2C%20the%20condition%20and%20aspiration%20for%20which%20they%20had%20been%20fighting%20since%201931%20would%20be%20fulfilled.%20So%20I%20thought%20that%20this%20would%20be%20a%20good%20compromise%20and%20I%20could%20retain%20the%20confidence%20of%20the%20people.%20Unfortunately%20communal%20forces%20and%20the%20trend%20in%20India%20which%20believed%20in%20a%20theocratic%20Hindu%20state%20proved%20to%20be%20too%20strong.%20And%20there%20was%20a%20break.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07143809%2FSheikh_Abdullah_with_other_leaders_of_1931_agitation.1931Photo.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07143809%2FSheikh_Abdullah_with_other_leaders_of_1931_agitation.1931Photo.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07143809%2FSheikh_Abdullah_with_other_leaders_of_1931_agitation.1931Photo-300x246.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666978%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESheikh%20Abdullah%20with%20other%20leaders%20of%20the%201931%20agitation.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20are%20referring%20to%201953%3F%20But%20you%20were%20very%20successful%20in%20doing%20so%20during%20the%20emergency%20(raiders%E2%80%99%20invasion).%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20time%20there%20was%20imminent%20danger.%20In%20Kashmir%2C%20in%20spite%20of%20everything%2C%20people%20do%20not%20believe%20in%20violence%20and%20communal%20hatred.%20They%20belong%20to%20the%20same%20ethnic%20group.%20There%20are%20people%2C%20both%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%2C%20who%20belong%20to%20the%20same%20caste%20and%20have%20the%20same%20surname%20%E2%80%93%20for%20example%20Bakshis%20are%20both%20Hindus%20and%20Muslim.%20Wattals%20are%20both%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20So%20there%20was%20nothing%20that%20could%20separate%20them%2C%20and%20this%20helped%20us%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20was%20the%20result%20you%20would%20have%20wanted%20to%20see%20emerge%20from%20a%20plebiscite%3F%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20time%20we%20thought%20that%20they%20could%20fulfil%20their%20ambitions%20by%20remaining%20a%20part%20of%20a%20democratic%20country%20in%20India%20because%20of%20Pandit%20Nehru%20and%20Gandhi%20and%20other%20Congressmen%20with%20whom%20we%20had%20close%20associations.%20We%20thought%20we%20too%20could%20remain%20a%20part%20of%20that%20country%20The%20sympathy%20of%20the%20Congress%20leaders%20for%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%20was%20fresh%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20the%20Kashmiris%20%E2%80%93%20how%20Nehru%20had%20suffered%20for%20them%20and%20Gandhi%20had%20sympathised%20with%20them.%20Though%20the%20ruler%20was%20a%20Hindu%20and%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20population%20was%20Muslim%2C%20this%20had%20not%20prevented%20the%20Congress%20leadership%20from%20identifying%20itself%20with%20the%20political%20movement%20in%20Kashmir%20led%20mainly%20by%20the%20Muslims.%20This%20had%20a%20tremendous%20impact%20on%20(Kashmiri)%20Muslims%20at%20that%20time.%20If%20a%20plebiscite%20had%20been%20conducted%20at%20that%20time%2C%20I%20am%20sure%20that%20it%20would%20have%20gone%20in%20favour%20of%20India.%20Later%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20situation%20changed%2C%20unfortunately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDid%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20army%20create%20tensions%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20very%20beginning%20we%20had%20to%20go%20through%20a%20lot%20of%20stress%20and%20strain%20even%20in%201947.%20When%20the%20first%20Indian%20Army%20troops%20came%20there%2C%20some%20of%20the%20battalions%20had%20completely%20lost%20their%20perspective.%20They%20thought%20that%20the%20fight%20was%20between%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%2C%20no%20matter%20where%20the%20Muslim%20belonged%20to.%20We%20had%20to%20face%20this%20trouble%20%5Bfrom%20the%20start%5D.%20A%20Sikh%20regiment%20from%20Patiala%20was%20stationed%20near%20the%20airport%20and%20wanted%20some%20volunteers.%20But%20the%20next%20morning%20when%20the%20camp%20moved%20out%2C%20we%20found%20the%20four%20volunteers%20dead%20in%20their%20bunkers.%20We%20had%20to%20face%20a%20terrible%20row%20in%20the%20city%20at%20that%20time.%20Then%20I%20called%20a%20conference%20and%20said%20that%20%5Bthe%20soldiers%20had%20perhaps%5D%20seen%20their%20nearest%20and%20dearest%20being%20killed%20in%20the%20riots.%20They%20were%20not%20in%20their%20normal%20mood%20as%20they%20thought%20that%20every%20Muslim%20was%20an%20enemy.%20They%20did%20not%20know%20that%20we%20were%20fighting%20for%20a%20certain%20cause.%20So%20we%20decided%20that%20the%20army%20heads%20and%20leaders%20must%20be%20told%20to%20inform%20the%20soldiers%20that%20they%20were%20fighting%20for%20an%20ideal.%20We%20did%20this%20and%20it%20had%20a%20very%20good%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDuring%20the%20period%20after%20the%20%5BKashmir%5D%20war%2C%20how%20did%20reactionary%20forces%2C%20which%20you%20said%20earlier%20proved%20to%20be%20too%20strong%2C%20manifest%20themselves%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20took%20over%20the%20administration%2C%20we%20had%20naturally%20to%20fulfil%20the%20promises%20we%20had%20made%20to%20the%20people%20for%20a%20long%20time%20about%20land%20reforms%2C%20the%20reduction%20and%20cancellation%20of%20debts%2C%20and%20other%20such%20reforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELandholdings%20were%20distributed%20among%20the%20tillers%20of%20the%20soil.%20Among%20the%20landlords%20there%20were%20Hindus%2C%20Muslims%20and%20others.%20But%20the%20Hindu%20landlords%20had%20a%20say%20in%20Delhi.%20They%20came%20here%20%5Bto%20Delhi%5D%20and%20spread%20poison%20against%20us%2C%20trying%20to%20give%20the%20land%20reforms%20a%20communal%20colour.%20There%20were%20people%20here%20who%20readily%20believed%20these%20people.%20This%20vitiated%20the%20atmosphere%20of%20relations%20between%20Kashmir%20and%20the%20Centre%2C%20giving%20them%20a%20communal%20cast%20when%20the%20object%20of%20our%20reforms%20was%20purely%20economic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%20with%20regard%20to%20debt%20cancellation.%20We%20passed%20a%20law%20according%20to%20which%20any%20debt%20in%20which%20the%20sum%20of%20interest%20payments%20had%20equalled%20or%20exceeded%20one%20and%20half%20times%20the%20value%20of%20the%20principal%20was%20considered%20automatically%20cancelled.%20Now%2C%20among%20the%20%3Cem%3Esahukars%3C%2Fem%3E%20(moneylenders)%20also%2C%20there%20were%20both%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims.%20The%20Hindu%20sahukars%20were%20able%2C%20and%20did%2C%20complain%20to%20people%20here%20in%20Delhi%2C%20thus%20further%20vitiating%20the%20atmosphere.%20And%20then%20the%20Maharaja%E2%80%A6we%20could%20not%20keep%20on%20the%20dynasty%E2%80%A6%20When%20the%20dynasty%20was%20abolished%2C%20all%20those%20people%20who%20used%20to%20surround%20the%20Maharaja%20took%20advantage%20of%20this%20position%2C%20did%20not%20like%20the%20changes%20my%20government%20was%20making%20and%20combined%20to%20wage%20a%20campaign%20on%20communal%20lines%20in%20Delhi%2C%20in%20spite%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20none%20of%20the%20measures%20we%20had%20passed%20were%20communally%20motivated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWas%20there%20any%20kind%20of%20discrimination%20in%20the%20allocation%20of%20jobs%20in%20Kashmir%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20time%20there%20was%20none%2C%20but%20one%20thing%20was%20clear%3A%20with%20the%20spread%20of%20education%2C%20groups%20which%20were%20not%20previously%20represented%20began%20to%20claim%20jobs.%20So%20we%20had%20to%20satisfy%20their%20urges.%20Muslims%2C%20who%20were%20as%20you%20know%20a%20majority%2C%20had%20suffered%20for%20a%20long%20time%20and%20were%20nowhere%20represented%20in%20the%20administration.%20So%20naturally%20when%20they%20came%20up%2C%20they%20expected%20that%20they%20would%20also%20get%20their%20due.%20This%20is%20what%20happened%20in%20Hyderabad%2C%20where%20the%20Hindus%20came%20up%20in%20a%20similar%20manner.%20The%20position%20in%20Kashmir%20was%20exactly%20the%20reverse%20of%20Hyderabad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20difficulty%2C%20however%2C%20was%20that%20I%20could%20not%20clean%20up%20the%20administration%20all%20at%20once.%20I%20could%20not%20remove%20people%20who%20had%20been%20working%20for%20years%20without%20providing%20them%20alternative%20employment.%20So%2C%20I%20was%20trying%2C%20little%20by%20little%2C%20to%20redress%20the%20balance%20of%20the%20various%20communities%20in%20government.%20The%20process%20was%20slow%2C%20but%20I%20can%20say%20with%20certainty%20that%20there%20was%20no%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOne%20often%20hears%20in%20Delhi%20that%20you%20were%20arrested%20on%20the%208th%20of%20August%2C%201953%20because%20you%20were%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20giving%20a%20unilateral%20call%20for%20independence.%20It%20is%20also%20said%20that%20you%20would%20have%20done%20so%20in%20your%20in%20speech%20on%201%20August.%20I%20have%20read%20the%20text%20of%20the%20speech%20which%20you%20were%20to%20give%20and%20have%20not%20found%20anything%20to%20support%20this%20thesis.%20Was%20there%20anything%20else%20which%20could%20have%20led%20to%20this%20conclusion%3F%20Did%20you%20at%20any%20point%20even%20consider%20such%20a%20unilateral%20declaration%20could%20not%20happen%3F%20What%20was%20the%20dialogue%20you%20were%20engaged%20in%20with%20Panditji%20at%20the%20time%20of%20your%20arrest%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPanditji%20wanted%20the%20ratification%20of%20the%20accession%20by%20the%20Kashmir%20Constituent%20Assembly.%20I%20advised%20him%20that%20the%20world%20would%20not%20accept%20this%20situation%2C%20nor%20the%20people%20whom%20we%20had%20been%20assuring%20that%20theirs%20would%20be%20the%20final%20say.%20Actually%20I%20had%20suggested%20this%20course%20%5Bratification%20by%20the%20Assembly%20at%20an%20early%20stage%5D%20in%201950.%20At%20that%20time%20it%20was%20Panditji%20who%20had%20firmly%20refused%20to%20follow%20this%20course%2C%20saying%20that%20India%20was%20committed%20not%20only%20to%20the%20people%20but%20to%20the%20entire%20world%20to%20hold%20the%20plebiscite.%20This%20ratification%20was%20one%20of%20the%20purposes%20for%20which%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20had%20been%20called%20in%201950.%20But%20Pakistan%20and%20protested%20strongly%20to%20the%20Security%20Council%2C%20and%20India%20had%20assured%20the%20council%20twice%20through%20Sir%20Benegal%20Rao%2C%20who%20was%20the%20permanent%20representative%20to%20the%20UN%2C%20that%20India%20would%20abide%20by%20her%20commitments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMay%20I%20now%20come%20to%20the%20present%20day%20%5B1968%5D%2C%20and%20ask%20you%20a%20few%20questions%20on%20which%20there%20has%20been%20some%20controversy%20recently%3A%20Firstly%2C%20quite%20a%20lot%20has%20been%20made%20in%20the%20press%20of%20your%20hesitation%20to%20declare%20your%20nationality%20as%20Indian.%20You%20subsequently%20clarified%20your%20position%20by%20saying%20that%20you%20were%20%E2%80%9Cprovisionally%E2%80%9D%20an%20Indian%20citizen%2C%20which%20did%20not%20really%20help%20very%20much.%20Would%20you%20care%20to%20tell%20me%20what%20made%20you%20hesitate%20to%20commit%20yourself%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20difficulty%20with%20me%20is%20that%20circumstances%20have%20drawn%20me%20into%20politics.%20Otherwise%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20feel%20myself%20good%20enough%20for%20this%20job.%20Because%20nowadays%20I%20feel%20a%20politician%20must%20know%20how%20to%20stab%20his%20friends.%20A%20politician%20must%20know%20all%20these%20dirty%20tricks.%20I%20find%20myself%20incapable%20of%20conspiracy%2C%20incapable%20of%20speaking%20untruths%2C%20and%20incapable%20of%20what%20we%20call%20diplomacy.%20I%20have%20suffered%20because%20of%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20regard%20to%20this%20nationality%20question%2C%20in%20my%20press%20conference%20my%20main%20objection%20was%20to%20the%20attitude%20of%20the%20questioner.%20I%20felt%20that%20he%20was%20not%20asking%20this%20question%20with%20a%20good%20intention%2C%20Otherwise%20I%20would%20have%20explained%20the%20whole%20position%20then%20and%20there.%20And%20what%20I%20thought%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20true%3B%20this%20question%20was%20loaded%2C%20and%20was%20meant%20to%20spoil%20the%20atmosphere%20of%20the%20conference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20regard%20to%20my%20nationality%2C%20I%20feel%20that%20this%20is%20the%20whole%20question%20under%20dispute%20since%201947.%20If%20the%20nationality%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20is%20considered%20fixed%20once%20and%20for%20all%2C%20then%20there%20is%20no%20dispute%20left%2C%20and%20nothing%20to%20be%20settled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20no%20one%20today%20seriously%20believes%20that%20there%20is%20no%20dispute.%20Even%20in%201965%20when%20the%20war%20was%20going%20on%2C%20Vinobaji%20%5BVinoba%20Bhave%5D%20is%20on%20record%20as%20having%20said%20that%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20dispute%20can%20only%20be%20considered%20truly%20settled%20when%20the%20people%20of%20India%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Pakistan%20and%20the%20whole%20world%20agree%20that%20it%20is%20settled.%20So%20at%20the%20most%2C%20as%20far%20as%20I%20am%20concerned%E2%80%A6you%20see%2C%20I%20have%20been%20a%20party%20to%20the%20provisional%20accession%2C%20so%20if%20you%20take%20it%20from%20a%20purely%20legalistic%20point%20of%20view%20then%20I%20consider%20myself%20as%20having%20accepted%20a%20provisional%20citizenship%20of%20Indian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07143949%2FIMAGE_1658936758.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07143949%2FIMAGE_1658936758.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07143949%2FIMAGE_1658936758-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07143949%2FIMAGE_1658936758-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666979%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESheikh%20Abdullah%20and%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20point%20is%20that%20we%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20of%20all%20shades%2C%20believe%20that%20so%20long%20as%20the%20uncertainty%20of%20the%20external%20situation%20continues%2C%20we%20can%20never%20have%20internal%20peace%20and%20stability.%20That%20has%20been%20our%20experience%20%E2%80%93%20not%20only%20mine%20but%20also%20of%20all%20my%20colleagues%2C%20including%20those%20who%20succeeded%20me.%20I%20have%20not%20been%20on%20the%20scene%20for%20the%20last%2014%20years%2C%20but%20all%20the%20material%20and%20moral%20help%20which%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20has%20given%20to%20Kashmir%20has%20not%20succeeded%20in%20bringing%20peace%20or%20stability.%20So%20we%20feel%20that%20peace%20and%20stability%20will%20only%20come%20when%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20come%20together%2C%20become%20friends.%20So%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%20have%20a%20self%20interest%20in%20seeing%20that%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20come%20together.%20I%20am%20working%20therefore%20for%20this%20purpose.%20So%20if%20you%20%E2%80%9Cfix%E2%80%9D%20me%2C%20then%20where%20is%20the%20basis%20on%20which%20I%20can%20work%20for%20better%20relations%3F%20I%20must%20have%20a%20little%20freedom%20to%20negotiate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98The%20third%20point%20which%20I%20keep%20trying%20to%20explain%20to%20my%20friends%20in%20India%20is%20that%20in%201947%2C%20Kashmir%20did%20not%20come%20to%20India%20because%20of%20any%20pressure%20or%20persuasion%2C%20but%20of%20its%20own%20free%20will.%20It%20was%20because%20we%20felt%20that%20our%20ambitions%20and%20our%20hopes%2C%20for%20which%20we%20had%20made%20huge%20sacrifices%20since%201931%2C%20would%20be%20fulfilled%20by%20allying%20ourselves%20with%20the%20great%20country%20which%20was%20India%2C%20which%20believed%20in%20democracy%2C%20in%20the%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20which%20believed%20in%20equality%20of%20man.%20We%20believe%20in%20the%20high%20ideals%20which%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20preached.%20Now%20look%20at%20the%20treatment%20Kashmir%20has%20received.%20That%20is%20an%20open%20book%2C%20and%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20go%20into%20it.%20Let%20every%20Indian%20search%20his%20own%20heart.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20most%20people%20in%20Indian%20seem%20to%20think%20that%20the%20Kashmiris%20enjoy%20the%20same%20degree%20of%20democracy%20which%20Indians%20elsewhere%20do.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20wish%20Kashmir%20had%20that%20democratic%20constitution%20and%20that%20democratic%20way%20of%20life%2C%20but%20the%20fact%20remains%20that%20Indian%20democracy%20stops%20short%20at%20Pathankot.%20Between%20Pathankot%20and%20Banihal%20you%20may%20have%20some%20measure%20of%20democracy%2C%20but%20after%20Banihal%20there%20is%20none.%20What%20we%20have%20in%20Kashmir%20bears%20some%20of%20the%20worst%20characteristics%20of%20colonial%20rule.%20We%20are%20at%20the%20mercy%20of%20an%20ordinary%20police%20officer.%20Nobody%20can%20express%20his%20opinion%20freely.%20Let%20any%20Indian%20go%20there%20and%20honestly%20assess%20the%20entire%20situation.%20Can%20you%20blame%20Kashmiris%20for%20saying%20that%20when%20the%20Indian%20government%20has%20kept%20their%20leader%2C%20Sheikh%20Mohammed%20Abdullah%2C%20in%20jail%20for%2014%20years%20without%20a%20charge%2C%20what%20can%20they%20expect%20from%20it%20in%20the%20future%20in%20the%20way%20of%20fair%20play%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20did%20not%20come%20%5Baccede%5D%20to%20Indian%20because%20of%20its%20vastness%2C%20or%20because%20it%20is%20a%20moneyed%20country.%20We%20were%20enamoured%20of%20the%20high%20principles%20for%20which%20you%20stood.%20But%20today%2C%20let%20alone%20what%20is%20happening%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20even%20here%20I%20have%20been%20released%20but%20I%20am%20discouraged%20from%20speaking%20of%20my%20cause.%20What%20happened%20in%20Meerut%3F%20The%20chief%20minister%20of%20UP%20directed%20all%20his%20district%20magistrates%20to%20prevent%20me%20from%20speaking%20if%20he%20felt%20this%20would%20lead%20to%20disturbances.%20The%20chief%20minister%20did%20not%20bother%20to%20find%20out%20who%20were%20the%20troublemakers%20in%20Meerut.%20What%20did%20I%20say%20at%20that%20public%20meeting%3F%20I%20delivered%20an%20address%20of%20nearly%20two%20and%20a%20half%20hours.%20The%20speech%20is%20there.%20I%20could%20be%20taken%20to%20task%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20that%20speech%2C%20but%20even%20there%20in%20Meerut%20when%20the%20atmosphere%20was%20so%20tense%2C%20I%20preached%20communal%20harmony.%20Does%20it%20become%20a%20minister%20in%20a%20democratic%20country%20to%20take%20such%20an%20attitude%3F%20Now%20I%20am%20warned%20not%20to%20go%20here%2C%20not%20to%20go%20there%2C%20not%20to%20go%20there%E2%80%A6this%20how%20Indian%20democracy%20functions.%20How%20do%20you%20expect%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%20today%20to%20come%20rushing%20to%20you%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%20India%20can%20keep%20Kashmir%20by%20force.%20But%20this%20way%20it%20will%20have%20the%20bodies%20of%20the%20Kashmiris%20but%20not%20their%20souls.%20That%20would%20not%20be%20a%20true%20accession.%20Accession%20should%20be%20of%20minds%20and%20hearts%2C%20and%20love%20and%20justice%20are%20the%20only%20two%20weapons%20which%20come%20with%20you%20for%20that%20accession.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20your%20public%20meetings%20and%20your%20talks%2C%20have%20you%20found%20the%20people%20more%20responsive%20to%20your%20suggestions%20than%20before%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20the%20common%20people%20are%20concerned%2C%20I%20have%20found%20them%20very%20responsive.%20They%20understand%20things%2C%20they%20are%20themselves%20tired%20of%20these%20people%20who%20exploit%20them%2C%20who%20try%20to%20exploit%20their%20emotions.%20There%20is%20a%20good%20response%20from%20the%20people.%20It%20is%20only%20gangs%20of%20assassins%2C%20who%20have%20learnt%20the%20art%20of%20murder%2C%20who%20have%20been%20taught%20how%20to%20stab%20people.%20These%20people%20hide%20in%20a%20bush%20and%20when%20a%20person%20is%20walking%20unawares%2C%20come%20up%20behind%20him%2C%20stab%20him%2C%20and%20run%20away.%20But%20not%20a%20single%20man%20has%20been%20caught%2C%20although%20in%20Meerut%20nearly%2030%20people%20have%20been%20stabbed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20disturbances%20in%20many%20places%20%E2%80%93%20Rourkela%2C%20Ranchi%2C%20even%20Srinagar.%20Hundreds%20of%20people%20have%20been%20involved%2C%20but%20no%20one%20has%20been%20hanged%20for%20murder%20committed%20during%20communal%20disturbances.%20I%20know%20very%20well%20that%20this%20is%20not%20representative%20of%20what%20is%20happening%20in%20the%20whole%20of%20India%2C%20and%20that%20India%20is%20a%20vast%20country%2C%20but%20these%20things%20are%20happening%2C%20and%20they%20have%20a%20terrible%20effect%20on%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20some%20Kashmiri%20students%20studying%20in%20Ranchi%20in%20the%20medical%20college%20there.%20They%20returned%20home%20almost%20naked.%20When%20they%20reached%20their%20home%2C%20they%20narrated%20their%20tale%20of%20misery%20and%20woe%20to%20the%20people.%20How%20could%20these%20things%20not%20effect%20the%20listeners%2C%20and%20how%20could%20you%20expect%20them%20to%20look%20to%20India%20for%20protection%3F%20These%20things%20have%20got%20to%20stop%2C%20but%20they%20will%20never%20stop%20until%20the%20tension%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20is%20resolved.%20There%20is%20only%20one%20answer%20to%20this%20problem%20and%20that%20is%20to%20end%20the%20strife%20on%20the%20subcontinent.%20How%20long%20can%20this%20be%20avoided%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20interview%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20February%2017%2C%201968%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3EWeekend%20Review%20%3Cem%3Eand%20is%20republished%20here%20courtesy%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3EHindustan%20Times%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3